			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-870057">
									

<p>Intresting idea, a little vague, but not bad, seems to add to it. Reminds me of Ice-9 a bit. I was a bit confused by the possible "Emergency Cryogenic Containment Protocol" use. If it's for people, then they'll just be effected, but if it's for items, seems that a container of liquid nitrogen would be more effective.</p>
<p>Also, Some of the descriptions seems a bit wordy, the line about needing a "sustained exothermic chemical reaction of significant temperature" to melt the ice stuck out the most. Does it need to be a chemical reaction? Will a blowtorch work? Also, what happens to the melted substance? does it turn to water, or instantly re-freeze as soon as the heat is removed?</p>
<p>All in all, an interesting idea, I'll be keeping an eye on it.</p>

